# GitHub Actions self-hosted runner configuration for ClusterOS
#
# This enables org-scoped runners that auto-scale from 0 to 4 pods inside k3s.
# Jobs consume cluster resources only while running; idle cost is zero.
#
# Setup (one-time):
#
#   1. Create a GitHub Personal Access Token (classic):
#      https://github.com/settings/tokens → Generate new token (classic)
#      Required scope: admin:org
#      (Fine-grained tokens do NOT yet support self-hosted runner registration)
#
#   2. Copy this file to patch/github.env and fill in the values below.
#
#   3. Run: make deploy
#      apply-patch.sh installs the file to /etc/clusteros/github.env (mode 600).
#      node-agent deploys ARC on the next leader start.
#
# Using runners in a workflow:
#
#   jobs:
#     build:
#       runs-on: clusteros-runner
#
# The runner label is "clusteros-runner" (set by runnerScaleSetName in server.go).
# Any repo in the org can use it without further configuration.

GITHUB_ORG=
GITHUB_PAT=
